==English==
===Pronunciation===
*pûr'zhən, /ˈpɜː(r)ʒən/, /<tt>"p3:(r)Z@n</tt>/
*pûr'shən, /ˈpɜː(r)ʃən/, /<tt>"p3:(r)S@n</tt>/

===Noun===
'''Persian''' ([[Persians]])

# the [[Farsi]] language. 
# a person from [[Persia]] (now [[Iran]]) or of Persian descent.
# a speaker of a Persian language, though almost always meant to refer to [[Farsi]] or its dialects. 
# a family of languages (often mutually intellegible) spoken in Iran, Afghanistan, Tajikistan, parts of Uzbekistan and Kurdish areas of Turkey, Iran and Iraq. This language family is part of the [[Indo-Iranian]] branch of the [[Indo-European]] language family. 



==Adjective==
Describes a person, place or object referring to Persia or Persians.


